# t/research/codex-lifecycle.test — the decision-004-critical Codex home lifecycle,
# exercised WITHOUT a live codex and WITHOUT resolving *Codex through the harness
# registry (decision-025). The whole real-Codex home/auth/skills/finalize core is
# gated on h.(*Codex), which no test ring resolves — and the merge gate forbids
# *_test.go (the scripts are the tests, docs/12) — so this one vocab line runs the
# Go-level assertions against the lifecycle's pure and package-internal seams.
#
# codex-lifecycle asserts, and fails the scenario if any breaks:
#   - per-task home path derivation ($STATE/codex/<taskID>), inert on an empty root;
#   - materialize the credential from the reserved secret as a 0600 auth.json;
#   - a MINIMAL config.toml (no host API-key/provider/MCP bleed over the OAuth login);
#   - REUSE across resume turns — the same home, codex's sessions/ store survives;
#   - no plaintext credential blob rides the env (only the DIR PATH does);
#   - rotation write-back ONLY when the operator is still connected, and audited —
#     never resurrecting a signed-out secret, never on an unchanged token;
#   - finalize does NOT remove the home (it persists across the task's turns);
#   - teardown on task-finish deletes the home and its 0600 credential;
#   - the boot sweep reaps a done/absent task's orphan home but keeps a live one.
#
# It drives no App messages, so the standing replay-convergence check passes trivially
# and the twin rings and their cassettes stay byte-identical.

codex-lifecycle
